The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 North Bengal varsity

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Calcutta, March 22: Finance minister Asim Dasgupta today announced that a university will be set up in north Bengal, and the location will be decided after talking to public representatives. 

 There will be a full-fledg-ed state university in nor-th Bengal. The place will be decided after consulting peoples representatives. There will be no restrictions on recruitment of teachers and non-teaching employees, he said.

 In his reply to the budget debate, Dasgupta also promised that remuneration of government-empanelled lawyers of all courts will be raised and payment of arrears expedited. The minister also announced that tobacco leaves have been exempted from VAT.

 DA rise

 After the merger of dearness allowance up to 50 per cent with basic pay, the remaining DA 21 per cent till March 31, and 24 per cent with effect from April 1 will be calculated on the revised basic sal-ary, Dasgupta said. The budget raised the DA from 71 per cent to 74 per cent from April 1. 




